Azure Role-Based Access Control (RBAC) is a system that manages access to Azure resources based on roles assigned to users, groups, or applications.

Common roles include:

* Owner: Full access
* Contributor: Can manage resources but not grant access
* Reader: View-only access

RBAC can be applied at different scopes such as managements group, subscription, resource group, or resource levels.

For example, a developer can be given Contributor access to a resource group but not to the entire subscription.

A real-life use case is separating duties in an organization. Security teams may have read-only access, while DevOps teams manage deployments.

Another example is multi-team collaboration where each team has controlled access to only their resources.

RBAC ensures security, accountability, and least-privilege access.
